<plot>Over the course of one year, solo journalist Kevin Sites covered 22 conflict zones in 19 countries, seeking to understand the real costs of a world perpetually at war. He learned a simple, but declarative truth: war is not about combatants and the clashing of armies, but about the systematic destruction of civil life -- one victim at a time.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?018585</url></doc>
